1089	 * @property {string} [hypothesis_template="This example is {}."] The template used to turn each
1090	 * candidate label into an NLI-style hypothesis. The candidate label will replace the {} placeholder.
1091	 * @property {boolean} [multi_label=false] Whether or not multiple candidate labels can be true.
1092	 * If `false`, the scores are normalized such that the sum of the label likelihoods for each sequence
1093	 * is 1. If `true`, the labels are considered independent and probabilities are normalized for each
1094	 * candidate by doing a softmax of the entailment score vs. the contradiction score.
1095	 *
1096	 * @callback ZeroShotClassificationPipelineCallback Classify the sequence(s) given as inputs.
1097	 * @param {string|string[]} texts The sequence(s) to classify, will be truncated if the model input is too large.
1098	 * @param {string|string[]} candidate_labels The set of possible class labels to classify each sequence into.
1099	 * Can be a single label, a string of comma-separated labels, or a list of labels.
1100	 * @param {ZeroShotClassificationPipelineOptions} [options] The options to use for zero-shot classification.
1101	 * @returns {Promise<ZeroShotClassificationOutput|ZeroShotClassificationOutput[]>} An array or object containing the predicted labels and scores.
1102	 *
1103	 * @typedef {TextPipelineConstructorArgs & ZeroShotClassificationPipelineCallback & Disposable} ZeroShotClassificationPipelineType
1104	 */
