1106	/**
1107	 * NLI-based zero-shot classification pipeline using a `ModelForSequenceClassification`
1108	 * trained on NLI (natural language inference) tasks. Equivalent of `text-classification`
1109	 * pipelines, but these models don't require a hardcoded number of potential classes, they
1110	 * can be chosen at runtime. It usually means it's slower but it is **much** more flexible.
1111	 *
1112	 * **Example:** Zero shot classification with `Xenova/mobilebert-uncased-mnli`.
1113	 * ```javascript
1114	 * const classifier = await pipeline('zero-shot-classification', 'Xenova/mobilebert-uncased-mnli');
1115	 * const text = 'Last week I upgraded my iOS version and ever since then my phone has been overheating whenever I use your app.';
1116	 * const labels = [ 'mobile', 'billing', 'website', 'account access' ];
1117	 * const output = await classifier(text, labels);
1118	 * // {
1119	 * //   sequence: 'Last week I upgraded my iOS version and ever since then my phone has been overheating whenever I use your app.',
1120	 * //   labels: [ 'mobile', 'website', 'billing', 'account access' ],
1121	 * //   scores: [ 0.5562091040482018, 0.1843621307860853, 0.13942646639336376, 0.12000229877234923 ]
1122	 * // }
1123	 * ```
1124	 *
1125	 * **Example:** Zero shot classification with `Xenova/nli-deberta-v3-xsmall` (multi-label).
1126	 * ```javascript
1127	 * const classifier = await pipeline('zero-shot-classification', 'Xenova/nli-deberta-v3-xsmall');
1128	 * const text = 'I have a problem with my iphone that needs to be resolved asap!';
1129	 * const labels = [ 'urgent', 'not urgent', 'phone', 'tablet', 'computer' ];
1130	 * const output = await classifier(text, labels, { multi_label: true });
1131	 * // {
